  "description": "The Reliquary Strongroom forms the secured storage core behind The Gloam Reliquary’s screened counter, built as a ferrocrete cell faced with void-black adamantine panels. Racked shelving and sealed lockboxes fill the walls in regimented tiers, each bay stenciled with lot codes and crossed by waxed purity seals. Cold lumen bars and auspex housings hold the space in clinical brightness, while the air remains sharp with decontamination agents. The floor is scored with drain channels and containment markings, reflecting quarantine protocol and siege-grade inventory discipline.",
